[CC0 1.0 Universal (CC0 1.0) Public Domain Dedication](https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/legalcode)\n\nTo the extent possible under law, I, [insert your name], have waived all copyright and related or neighboring rights to this work.\n\nThis work is published from: [insert your country].\n\n### Summary\n\nThis is a human-readable summary of the Legal Code (read the full text at https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/legalcode) which is in the public domain. This means you can use it in any way that you want, and you don’t have to pay for it. It’s free and you can share it with others.\n\n### Effect\n\nYou can copy, modify, distribute and perform the work, even for commercial purposes, all without asking permission.\n\n### No Rights Reserved\n\nCC0 is a tool that allows creators to give up their copyright and dedicate their works to the public domain. It’s a universal approach that can be employed for nominally any form of creative work.